the archbishop of this smogchoked city 
has asked roman catholic faithful to pray for rain to relieve air 
pollution 
in a statement published by local newspapers friday monsignor 
carlos oviedo asked catholics to pray for the needed rain and to 
actively cooperate with the measures being ordered by the citys 
antipollution commission 
authorities say a downpour is badly needed to clean the air 
which has been thick for several weeks with fumes from motor 
vehicles and factories 
since last week the government has imposed a series of 
emergency measures that include banning 40 percent of all cars 
trucks and buses from downtown hospitals have reported a sharp 
increase in cases of respiratory disease 
no significant rainfall has been recorded in the santiago area 
since last year besides aggravating the smog problem the dry 
weather also threatens to produce a water shortage authorities say 
