president bush is sharing credit with mikhail s 
gorbachev for natos decision to tone down its warfighting 
doctrine saying the embattled soviet leader is entitled to declare 
ive been right in dealing with the west 
bush said gorbachev can boast that the 16nation nato alliance 
agreed to overhaul its strategy in direct response to 
sovietsanctioned democratic changes in eastern europe 
at the same time bush observed it was the united states 
draft that shaped the new direction for nato 
gorbachev should get on the offensive against soviet critics 
who are angry over the collapse of the warsaw pact and the pullback 
of red army troops bush suggested friday at the conclusion of 
natos twoday summit 
bush was in high spirits as he flew here for two days of 
diplomatic meetings and texasstyle celebrations before opening the 
annual economic summit of the seven largest industrial powers 
monday 
the president jetted to houston on a 10hour nonstop flight from 
london and the nato meeting which swiftly agreed to his blueprint 
for changes in western military doctrine to reflect the reduced 
military threat from moscow 
relaxing against the side of a seat on air force one bush could 
barely conceal his delight you saw what happened to us 
influence today he said pointing to the nato communique which 
incorporated his proposals 
despite his upbeat mood bush refused anew to declare the cold 
war over 
ive tried to avoid code words he said at a postsummit 
news conference the cold war being over is something that id 
rather not comment on 
i dont think were dealing in terms of victory and defeat 
he continued were dealing in terms of how do we stabilize and 
guarantee the peace and security of europe 
acting on bushs suggestions nato agreed to shrink its arsenal 
of battlefield nuclear weapons in tandem with soviet action and 
relegate them to highly unlikely lastresort use 
the nato leaders also said that once negotiations begin on 
shortrange nuclear forces the alliance will propose in return 
for reciprocal action by the soviet union the elimination of all 
its nuclear artillery shells from europe 
they also decided to field smaller and restructured ground 
forces in the newest sign that natos 40year job of containing 
potential sovietbloc aggression was nearing a successful end 
at his news conference bush said that gorbachev could point to 
the nato meeting and say they have now changed their doctrine 
because of steps that i mr gorbachev have taken 
if i were him bush said id say ive been right 
the president said he would discuss the nato meeting with 
gorbachev in a telephone call over the next couple weeks aboard 
his plane the president said he recently received a communication 
from gorbachev but bush merely winked and smiled when asked to 
elaborate 
despite prodding from some allies bush said he was not ready to 
join west germany and perhaps others in rushing financial aid to 
moscow to prop up gorbachev and his sickly economy financial 
assistance for the soviet union is expected to be a major topic of 
discussion at the economic summit 
i have some big problems with that one and i think the 
american people do bush said 
if the germans decide they want to do that thats their 
business he said but i have made very clear to those who have 
spoken to me about this that at this juncture we have some serious 
problems and ive not been under any false colors about that at 
all 
he said for example the soviet union is spending too much 
money on its military bush also complained that moscow is paying a 
5 billion subsidy to cuba each year to sustain a totalitarian 
regime that is highly critical of the soviet union from time to 
time 
while objecting to direct financial aid bush said perhaps 
there are ways we can assist them as we go forward with credit or 
other matters before we go to direct government loans 
