<TEXT>
here is a chronological look at some of the political changes in 
albania following world war i 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
1925 albania is declared a republic and ahmet beg zogu is 
elected president 
1928 zogu is proclaimed king zog 
1939 albania is occupied by italy 
1943 nazi german forces occupy the country 
1944 the communistled national liberation front established 
in 1941 with help from the yugoslav communists takes power 
1945 elections are held based on a single slate of candidates 
sponsored by the communists headed by enver hoxha 
1946 king zog is deposed and the peoples republic of albania 
is proclaimed 
1949 albania seeking protection from yugoslav expansionism 
joins the moscowbased council for mutual economic assistance or 
comecon 
1955 albania joins the warsaw pact 
1961 the soviet union denounces albanias ties with the 
beijing government and breaks off relations 
1962 albania withdraws from comecon and turns increasingly to 
china for support 
1968 albania withdraws from the warsaw pact 
1972 albania becomes disenchanted with the beijing government 
after relations improve between china and the united states 
1978 china formally terminates all economic and military 
support 
1982 the government stops an attempted coup by albanian 
exiles while not directly involved the pretender to the throne of 
albania admits knowing the rebels leader 
1985 hoxha dies and is replaced by ramiz alia who vows to 
continue hoxhas policies 
1989 despite the reforms sweeping away the repressive 
governments of eastern europe alia continues with the hardline 
communist government 
may 5 1990 greece recalls its ambassador from albania after 
accusing albanian security officials of pursuing an asylumseeker 
into the greek embassy beating him and dragging him away 
may 8 in a clear break with its long policy of isolation 
albania says it wants to join a 35nation security group the 
conference on secuerity and cooperation in europe and will allow 
freer travel for its citizens 
may 10 un secretarygeneral president javier perez de 
cuellar arrives for an unprecedented meeting with albanian 
officials 
june 6 albania pledges to adopt basic reforms short of free 
elections and seek equal status with the 35 nations that signed 
the helsinki security and human rights accords 
tuesday riots break out in tirana when albanians seek 
sanctuary in foreign embassies in an apparent attempt to flee the 
repressive regime 
wednesday foreign diplomats in albania ask a meeting with the 
government to discuss the fate of hundreds of albanians seeking 
refuge in foreign embassies 
friday police attack demonstrators near the embassy district 
alia offers no generosity for asylumseekers now said to 
number up to 4000 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

