devoted exclusively to poetry said lisa sornberger who recently 
returned to school at eastern connecticut state university in 
willimantic conn before her return she was recreation director 
at a home for retarded adults 
theres never enough time so i squeeze writing in when i 
can she said i write mostly in the car while im driving 
ive tried to keep a tape recorder but it picks up too much road 
noise 
to keep the poets off the streets bucknell began inviting them 
to its campus six years ago 
usually 50 to nearly 100 apply for the program submitting two 
letters of recommendation a letter of selfintroduction and 15 
pages of poetry only 10 writers are selected 
were not trying to teach a body of information were not 
even trying to teach a skill wheatcroft said were giving 
them an opportunity to develop themselves as poets we provide them 
with the environment and ambience for that 
an anonymous evaluation from a participant in one of the first 
five programs likened the seminar to a religious retreat in that 
everything felt sacred except that the religion was poetry 
sornberger wrote seven new pieces this year but none is a 
completed poem she said amy hickman of anderson sc who goes 
to goucher college in baltimore finished three and revised several 
she had done before arriving at bucknell 
for her reading friday night hickman prepared charlie and 
ruby junes champale party in which the heroes party in the back 
of a pickup truck knocking back rum and slurpees 
sornberger read aunt stella a composite of a lot of women 
i love 
even with an unpromising financial future from poetry hickman 
and sornberger said they couldnt quit writing it without losing 
part of themselves 
for instance when im not writing much i get very tense 
very on edge hickman said writing poetry is like making order 
of the world its sort of being like people who are obsessively 
neat 
jobs and other classwork are the main culprits stealing time 
from wouldbe poets wheatcroft said 
usually princes subsidized poets and in some countries the 
state subsidizes them in this country most poets have had some 
other job wheatcroft said ts eliot was in banking and william 
carlos williams was a pediatrician for example 
in undergraduate work usually students must divide themselves 
over four courses split their heads four different ways he 
said we wanted to provide them with a month to see what they 
could do 
