feeforservice seafood inspection program which uses a government 
inspection mark that program would continue to provide grading 
services but continuation of other parts of the program would 
depend on the extent to which companies switch to the new system 
officials said 
the new plan would be based on inspections at various critical 
points at which health risks such as spoilage and bacterial 
growth can be controlled the fda said companies would pay a fee 
for inspections and could earn an official mark or seal they could 
display on their products label 
