officials at the rocky flats nuclear 
weapons plant suspended handling of all nuclear materials because 
of lax security a us department of energy official said friday 
plutonium operations at the plant were halted in november while 
safety and management improvements were made at the plant the new 
ban applies to other rocky flats nuclear operations virtually all 
of which are classified 
the suspension went into effect thursday night following an 
annual inspection by members of the does albuquerque nm 
operations office according to rocky flats doe manager robert m 
nelson 
the plant 16 miles northwest of denver is the nations only 
source of plutonium triggers for nuclear weapons 
nelson said investigators discovered security at the plant could 
be breached investigators were sent in during the past few weeks 
to try to smuggle out pieces of metal such as plutonium and other 
securitysensitive materials he said 
nelson said the only line of defense that failed was a metal 
detector such as that used at airports and there were other lines 
of defense that caught the materials 
it wasnt like they could smuggle it off the plant site he 
said 
nelson said the deficiencies developed because workers were 
wearing steeltoed shoes required by federal regulations that kept 
setting off the metal detectors he said workers at the plant 
became frustrated at having to remove their shoes to pass through 
the detectors and security became lax 
he said there was no danger because of the security lapses and 
the problems have been corrected he said workers are now wearing 
fiberglasstoed shoes that dont trip the monitors 
maybe we overreacted when we shut down the plant he said 
they only made it through one line of defense but to me thats 
enough to stop everything 
nelson said other violations were found but none were 
showstoppers 
they included things like improper access to classified 
documents and improper handling of chemicals but he wouldnt be 
more specific 
