<TEXT>
a powerful aftershock jolted 
quakeshattered northwestern iran overnight panicking residents 
setting off landslides and injuring two people official media 
reported today 
the official islamic republic news agency also reported a tremor 
near the southern iranian city of yazd this morning but it was 
considerably less powerful than the aftershock in the north 
irna and tehran radio monitored in nicosia said the aftershock 
struck the city of rudbar in gilan province at 1105 pm friday 
335 am edt today tehran universitys geophysics center said 
it registered 59 on the richter scale 
more than 400 aftershocks have hit gilan since the devastating 
june 21 earthquake which killed about 40000 people injured 
60000 and left about half a million people homeless the initial 
quake was measured at between 73 and 77 on the richter scale 
the aftershock friday was felt in tehran but caused no 
casualties or damage in the iranian capital irna said 
the quake near yazd 370 miles from tehran measured 49 on the 
richter scale the center said 
the agency and the radio initially reported rudbar had been hit 
by a new earthquake but in later dispatches irna called it an 
aftershock 
irna said two people in rudbar were taken to hospitals for 
treatment the earthquakeflattened city has only makeshift relief 
clinics however 
the news agency said the aftershock triggered landslides in the 
mountainous region that blocked two main roads but it said crews 
immediately moved in and worked until the roads were cleared 
gilan and zanjan another agricultural province to its south 
bore the brunt of the june 21 quake 
the richter scale is a measure of ground motion as recorded on 
seismographs every increase of one number means a tenfold increase 
in magnitude an earthquake measuring 5 on the richter scale can 
cause considerable damage and one registering 6 can cause severe 
damage 
iranian interior minister abdollah nouri said this week that it 
would be overwhelmingly difficult to rebuild the 
earthquakestricken region 
the interior minister said iran needed to repair roads water 
systems and electrical service as well as replace buildings the 
cost just to repair residences and the water and electrical systems 
will be 1 billion he said 
he said 90000 residences had been damaged in the quake most of 
them were made of mud brick or kilndried brick with little 
reinforcement in the walls 
he said iran had two months to build shelter before the rainy 
season begins in september 
