<TEXT>
the governor of the troubled northern 
state of kashmir ordered an indefinite curfew in the capital 
effective today and gave the army full control of the battle 
against moslem separatists 
soldiers in camouflage uniforms manned checkpoints and patrolled 
in machinegun mounted jeeps strictly enforcing the curfew said 
residents who spoke on condition of anonymity 
the hindudominated government announced a special powers 
ordinance giving the army command of countering the moslem 
insurgency newspapers reported in the past the army was 
subordinate to the police and paramilitary forces 
residents said they feared the move could be the start of a 
fresh crackdown and more violence in the state which borders 
moslem pakistan 
jammukashmir gov girish saxena signed the order friday 
permitting army troops to conduct searches and destroy militant 
hideouts and ordering an indefinite curfew in srinagar the 
newspapers said 
on thursday saxena empowered security forces to fire at any 
suspected insurgent and search and destroy any building 
srinagar has been the focal point of the moslem movement for 
secession of the kashmir valley from hindumajority india 
at least 668 people have been killed in the picturesque 
himalayan valley since jan 20 when the government first ordered a 
crackdown on moslem insurgents 
however the insurrection has shown no signs of abating 
jammukashmir state is the only one of indias 25 states which 
has a moslem majority a separatist movement has been simmering in 
the kashmir valley since 1947 after its hindu ruler opted for 
union with india when the subcontinent was divided into 
hindumajority india and islamic pakistan 
the insurgency flared this year after moslem insurgents dropped 
their demand for union with pakistan and began agitating for 
independence and the status of an neutral nation 
the government responded by dismissing the state government and 
bringing the province under the federallyappointed governor 
on friday interior minister mufti mohammed sayeed said the 
state would be brought under direct federal rule from july 19 when 
six months of governors rule expires 
the decision is a technicality since gov saxena will remain 
the federal governments representative in the state but it 
indicates that the government has no immediate plans to hold 
elections to the state assembly 
under state law governors rule cannot be extended beyond six 
months but federal or presidents rule can remain in force for up 
to three years 
