south korea may join north korea in 
opening a strip of border for the first time in four decades an 
influential newspaper said today 
north korea said friday it would open a portion of its frontier 
at the truce village of panmunjom on aug 15 in order to promote 
korean unity and called on south korea to do the same 
south korea initially dismissed the move as propaganda but the 
donga ilbo newspaper quoting an unidentified government official 
said today that seoul was reconsidering 
also today kim daejung south koreas bestknown opposition 
politician expressed support for the north korean move and asked 
the seoul government to broaden contact with north korea at all 
levels 
kim addressing a rally also urged the seoul government to 
accept a north korean proposal to share a single seat in the united 
nations with rotating representation 
in another development today south korean officials said north 
korea agreed to reopen talks aimed at setting up a joint meeting of 
lawmakers from the capitalist south and the communist north the 
talks suspended since january were to resume july 19 
longtime observers expressed hopes that this weeks developments 
could lead to an easing of tensions between the koreas the 
peninsula has been divided since 1945 
northsouth negotiators agreed in principle this week to meet 
july 26 to sign accords for a historic first meeting of prime 
ministers of the two nations the talks are expected to be held in 
seoul in august 
north korea said friday it would open an 800yard stretch of 
border at panmunjom a truce village inside the 25milewide 
demilitarized zone on aug 15 korea was liberated from japan on 
that date in 1945 
panmunjom is an ovalshaped enclave straddling a western portion 
of the 155mile border between the two koreas it is where military 
officials of both sides meet to discuss alleged armistice 
violations the area is offlimits to civilians 
north korea said it would not allow outsiders to travel into the 
north beyond the perimeter of panmunjom 
the initial south korean response was negative but donga said 
some within the government were rethinking their stance 
although the north korean move is believed to be propaganda 
we would not reject it totally we would rather use it to help ease 
tension and bring them to openness the paper quoted the 
unidentified official as saying 
the paper said the south korean government may reciprocate by 
opening its own sector of panmunjom and suggest that the border 
village be made a meeting place for 10 million separated family 
members in the two koreas 
south korea also may propose building a peace city jointly 
with north korea inside the demilitarized zone it said 
north korea has rejected similar proposals in the past 
seoul officials said they suspect that the north korean move is 
aimed at encouraging south korean dissidents to hold a unification 
rally at panmunjom on aug 15 
a major south korean dissident group chonminyon welcomed the 
north korean announcement and said it will send 300 delegates to 
meet with north koreans that day 
the seoul government bans unauthorized contact with north korea 
by its citizens it contends dialogue with the north koreans must 
be conducted through official channels 
