a strong earthquake jolted west java 
destroying or damaging more than 150 homes and buildings and 
killing one villager officials said saturday eleven people were 
injured 
the quake friday measured 52 on the richter scale of ground 
motion and was centered in a mountainous area of majalengka about 
185 miles southeast of the capital said sutarjo a government 
meterology official in jakarta 
the death and injuries all occurred in the anggarwati area near 
the epicenter said majalengka district administrator djufri 
pringadi 
the richter scale is a measure of ground motion as recorded on 
seismographs every increase of one number means a tenfold increase 
in magnitude thus a reading of 55 reflects an earthquake 10 times 
stronger than one of 45 
