<TEXT>
the state plans to resume aerial spraying of 
the pesticide malathion to eradicate mediterranean fruit flies this 
week despite a study that says the material contains toxic heavy 
metals 
state officials say their tests show theres no threat to public 
health 
helicopters will spray a 14squaremile area of los angeles on 
thursday state officials said friday the spraying was scheduled 
for last week but was delayed after city attorneys presented the 
findings of their analysis 
the mediterranean fruit fly also called the medfly can destroy 
hundreds of varieties of fruits and vegetables and is considered a 
serious threat to the states multibilliondollar agriculture 
