samples of malathion contained excessive levels of lead nickel and 
chromium wachs said the presence of the metals violated strict 
state limits on toxic substances and said he would seek a temporary 
restraining order against the spraying monday 
truesdail laboratories in tustin calif conducted the 
independent analysis of malathion for the city of los angeles 
but state tests of the same samples found no dangerous levels of 
heavy metals state officials countered 
the numbers our lab got are very low in fact lower than that 
in plain old soil said james w stratton who headed the state 
department of health services review of the pesticide 
the department of health services has completed its latest 
test and like all previous tests has determined that our malathion 
spraying program poses no public health risk said henry j voss 
state agriculture director 
the downtown spraying was ordered after a single female medfly 
was found near dodger stadium 
malathion was last sprayed in southern california on june 26 in 
riverside and san bernardino counties 
the state also plans to release millions of sterilized male 
medflies in an effort to interfere with reproduction 
</TEXT>
