the louisiana senate today sustained 
gov buddy roemers veto of the nations toughest state abortion 
bill coming three votes shy of the number needed to override 
however the issue was not dead and a second vote on the issue 
is likely to be taken sunday under legislative rules the fact 
that a simple majority was in favor meant that backers can try for 
another vote on the issue sunday 
the vote in favor of the override was 2316 it takes 26 votes 
in the senate to override a veto 
the house voted to override friday 
the senators debated as chanting abortion foes and a few 
prochoice demonstrators gathered in the balcony in the capitol 
rotunda and outside at one point state troopers carried a 
