stefanis replacement ata reported 
ata also reported that three new figures were appointed to the 
politburo and two new appointments were made to the central 
committee 
the changes appeared to reflect the power of communist leader 
ramiz alia and his efforts to reform albanias hardline communist 
system 
also saturday alia decreed several measures to reform albanias 
command economy including the introduction of smallscale private 
enterprise limited to tradesmen and farmers he did not however 
mention the embassy standoff or promise political reforms 
speaking from tirana a hungarian diplomat said on condition of 
anonymity that police sealed off the diplomatic quarter saturday 
afternoon apparently to prevent new asylumseekers from gaining 
access to the missions 
the reported breakthrough came just hours after albanian 
legislators guaranteed citizens could leave the embassies without 
fear of punishment 
