passports to those who have sought refuge in foreign missions 
but saturdays parliamentary decree published by the albanian 
state news agency ata was the first pledge with the force of law 
that albanians in the foreign missions could receive passports 
without fear or prosecution 
the thousands of albanians in the foreign embassies were a 
nearintolerable strain on some missions which lacked sufficient 
food and water albanian authorities were not allowing foreign 
governments to send supplies western officials said 
the hungarian diplomat who spoke on condition of anonymity said 
that under the deal worked out with authorities the albanians were 
to remain in the embassies until told their passports were ready 
on the day of their departure or on the day immediately 
preceding it they will be going in groups to the passport office 
to get documents and can be accompanied by embassy staffers he 
said 
diplomats will be invited to board the aircraft trains buses 
or boats taking albanians to their new homelands the diplomat 
said but only those accepted by a foreign country will be allowed 
to leave he said 
