in all albanians packing its embassy 
in the 45 years of hardline communist rule travel for average 
albanians has been virtually impossible 
but under alia who took power in 1985 the country of 32 
million people has increasingly sought ties abroad and has slowly 
begun to implement reforms 
a package of new regulations that took effect tuesday entitled 
all albanians over age 16 to own a passport 
the ata dispatch said the embassy occupations were calculated to 
create a state of tension and opposition to the laws and 
regulations of the albanian state 
this is also proved by the fact that some countries want to 
send here food tents medicaments so as to turn the yards of the 
embassies into refugees camps 
such brutal interference and antihuman acts are unacceptable 
and punishable ata said 
on friday alia told the central committee that the party would 
not give up power as communists have done elsewhere in eastern 
europe 
the sometimesviolent rush to the embassies in tirana follows 
last years exodus of east germans to embassies in other east 
european countries shortly before the fall of their communist 
government 
most of the albanians who fled to foreign embassies before 
thursday entered in a rush during rioting that began monday under 
fire from albanian security forces diplomats said at least three 
