friday from air force one giving bushs personal reflections on 
the nato summit and describing the changing nature of the 
military alliance 
previously gorbachev wrote bush to make his case for us 
economic aid us sources said the message was much the same as 
one gorbachev advanced recently to the leaders of west germany and 
france 
the bushkaifu meeting also touched on american domestic 
policies with the japanese leader praising bush for newfound 
willingness to consider tax increases in order to reduce americas 
budget deficit a japanese official said 
we believe the statement issued by president bush on june 26 
was very courageous taizo watanabe spokesman for the japanese 
finance ministry told reporters 
the federal budget deficits have long been a sore point with 
other summit countries who contend that excessive american 
borrowing needs have driven up worldwide interest rates 
in addition to the united states and japan the other countries 
at the economic summit are west germany britian france italy and 
canada 
the world leaders were not spending all of their time discussing 
serious subjects bush was treating the summit leaders to a 
countrystyle barbecue rodeo and performance by the grand ole opry 
on sunday 
the city of houston anxious to show the world that it had 
rebounded after being flattened by the oil bust of 1982 raised 10 
million in donations and turned out an army of volunteers to assist 
visiting dignitaries and reporters 
last years economic summit was held in paris as part of the 
200th anniversary of the french revolution while houston boosters 
conceded that the houston summit would not top that affair they 
did try their best providing a texassyle welcome for each leader 
kaifu the first to arrive was greeted by a group of 
schoolchildren singing deep in the heart of texas in 
japanese with temperatures in the 90s and oppressive humidity 
kaifu and the other leaders had no trouble knowing they had arrived 
in houston 
before the start of his meeting with kaifu bush was asked 
whether he planned to pressure the japanese leader to drop his push 
to resume development loans to china this assistance was put on 
hold by agreement of the summit countries last year in paris in 
response to the brutal crackdown on the prodemocracy movement in 
tiananmen square 
bush indicated that the summit countries are likely to abandon 
their united front providing japan the opportunity to pursue its 
own lending policy 
japan bush said is a sovereign nation they can make up 
their own minds on a lot of questions 
the goitseparately approach was also likely to prevail on the 
contentious question over whether to provide direct economic aid to 
the soviet union west germany has already announced it will 
provide 31 billion in loans and economic assistance 
west germany france and italy have been pushing the allies to 
endorse a 15 billion economic aid package to bail out the 
floundering soviet economy but the united states and britain 
opposed providing direct economic aid until the soviets made a 
bolder move toward a freemarket economy and stopped siphoning 
large amounts of its resources into the military and support for 
cuba 
japan has its own special problem with soviet aid contending 
japanese assistance would be impossible until moscow has settled a 
45yearold territorial dispute over four islands north of japan 
that have been occupied by the soviet union since world war ii 
secretary of state james a baker iii said saturday that the 
summit scheduled to run from monday through wednesday was likely 
to conclude without a common position on soviet aid 
baker for the first time saturday discussed publicly a new us 
proposal to establish a multibilliondollar international aid 
program for latin america 
while details of the plan are sketchy it would be modeled after 
the economic aid package being offered to emerging democracies in 
eastern europe with the assistance coming from the same group of 24 
nations who are providing aid to eastern europe 
the latin american aid would be another effort by the bush 
administration to reassure new democratic governments in this 
hemisphere that they will not be overlooked in the rush to help 
eastern europe 
the united states received a warning saturday from an official 
of the 12nation european community that its heavy lobbying on 
elimination of farm subsidies could be counterproductive 
the united states is in a battle with european countries over a 
us proposal to phase out expensive farm subsidies over the next 
decade europeans contend that the request could cost the jobs of 
between 2 million and 3 million lessefficient european farmers 
bush has made resolution of the farm dispute a top priority for 
the houston summit believing that agreement in this area is 
crucial to the successful conclusion of 97nation effort to 
overhaul the entire world trading system those talks known as the 
uruguay round are scheduled to conclude in december 
