<TEXT>
a prominent state legislator has been 
convicted of conspiracy for inducing a former prison mate to invest 
in an illegal bingo operation then fleecing him of half the money 
a 12member jury convicted state rep tommy burnett on friday of 
nine conspiracy counts that carry a possible prison term of 45 
yearsno sentencing date was set by us district judge thomas a 
higgins 
two codefendants columbia businessman ee shutt and knoxville 
bingo operator virginia hurst were convicted on charges of 
conspiracy and operating a gambling enterprise 
burnett faces trial sept 11 on a related perjury charge 
the convictions were the first to result from a joint 
federalstate corruption probe that has produced indictments 
against 43 people including a former state representative an 
election commissioner a bingo regulator and various bingo 
operators 
the investigation has centered on misuse of profits from bingo 
which had been permitted in the state only to benefit charities 
and was made illegal altogether in 1989 partly as a result of the 
investigation 
while burnett was serving 10 months of a federal prison sentence 
