couple 
the hearing the first of its kind for the fledgling evangelical 
lutheran church in america could result in the expulsion of the 
local churches from the 53 millionmember denomination 
but the rev john frykman of first united lutheran church and 
the rev james delange of st francis lutheran church say they and 
their flocks are willing to be ousted to prove their support of the 
civil and religious rights of homosexuals 
gays and lesbians are the largest oppressed minority in this 
country frykman said the church for too long has betrayed gay 
and lesbian people and forced them to live as alienated people 
the threeday hearing before a 14member committee marks the 
first time the evangelical lutheran church in america has sought to 
discipline a pastor or congregation church officials said the 
church was formed in a merger of three major lutheran groups in 
january 1988 
the panel on monday may impose a penalty ranging from censure to 
suspension to expulsion 
that is a very painful kind of possibility to contemplate 
said sierra pacific synod bishop lyle miller who heads the church 
in northern california 
the evangelical lutheran church in america like most other 
mainstream churches forbids the ordination of sexually active gay 
men and lesbians 
we have standards for the ordained and one of them is that 
sexual activity is only to be practiced within the bonds of 
