<TEXT>
alan greenspan looks for zeros as patiently as a 
guy with a handful of quarters stationed in front of a slot 
machine but the combination he wants just doesnt come up 
greenspan wants zero inflation in the american economy and he 
is willing to battle the odds and take big risks in order to get 
it a lot of people think hell bust the economy in seeking that 
goal 
so be it chairman greenspan seems to say contending that if 
inflation isnt drawn out of the economy now it will simply 
reappear and scuttle the next economic advance deny it fuel 
suffocate the fires 
as head of the federal reserve board greenspan is effectively 
in charge of monetary policy his hands control the money supply 
the fuel and by keeping a firm hand on those levers he can force 
his will on the economy 
that is in pursuit of zero inflation he can slow the economy to 
the point where consumer willingness and ability to buy will 
diminish where producers will cut output where borrowing and 
lending will wane 
the big risk in seeking zero inflation is recession and many 
relatively wellinformed people think the economy is on the brink 
of it gross national product is barely growing job growth is down 
sharply manufacturing is weak 
true the service sector as opposed to the goodsproducing 
sector shows a moderate amount of vitality but those who worry 
about inflation observe that this same sector is where prices are 
still continuing to rise 
nobody really wants to see an economy declining everyone 
benefits from an economy that grows without inflation but too 
often greenspan supporters say growth has been diminished and 
then halted by inflation 
broadly speaking those who support the chairman in his war on 
inflation who encourage him to hold fast against pressures to 
lower interest rates which would spur economic activity have 
some solid grounds for so thinking 
in their view the coals of demandpull inflation still smolder 
that type of inflation occurs when easy money allows people to 
demand goods and services at a rate that cannot be sustained 
eventually the glowing coals flame up 
the zero inflationists believe the country may not be able to 
stand such an excess of activity given its inability to solve 
existing debt problems a consequence it should be noted of 
earlier excesses 
among the existing excesses are the federal budget deficit a 
consequence of excessive government spending the foreign trade 
