<TEXT>
if the rise of the stock market to record highs 
this year has produced a new wave of optimism in the business 
world you cant tell it by the level of activity in stock splits 
and dividend increases 
in textbook bull markets corporate boards of directors act in 
large numbers to celebrate the upward course of prosperity by 
voting a split or a higher dividend payout or both at the same 
time 
right now figures compiled by standard amp poors corp attest 
they are doing neither at anything like the rate of boom years in 
the past 
through the first half of 1990 sampp tallied 48 splits of at least 
three shares for two among the 1600plus companies listed on the 
new york stock exchange 
at that rate the total for the year might fall short of 
matching the 105 splits recorded in 1989 mounting no threat at 
all to the record of 225 set in 1983 
the story on dividends from all the public companies reporting 
to sampp is even less impressive 
the firm counted 868 favorable dividend actions increases 
resumptions of suspended dividends and declarations of extra or 
special payouts in the first half of this year down from 1155 
in the comparable period of 1989 
on the other side of the coin the number of unfavorable 
changes including reductions and omissions swelled to 187 in this 
years first half from 109 over the like period last year 
these figures point up two of the most common complaints voiced 
by wall streeters and their customers about the bull market 
1990style 
the paucity of splits demonstrates the narrowness of the 
recent market rally in the words of sampp analysts with much of 
the gains concentrated in a few dozen bigname blue chips and 
growth stocks 
sluggish dividend activity meanwhile spotlights persistent 
weakness in corporate earnings which has led to much doubt and 
skepticism about the staying power of the advance in stock prices 
a stock split represents a gesture by a companys directors with 
more symbolic than tangible value 
in a 2for1 split for example the number of shares 
outstanding is doubled cutting earnings per share in half and 
producing no change in the total market value of an investors 
holdings its comparable to receiving two 10 bills for a 20 
sampp notes 
splits can however broaden enthusiasm for a stock in the 
marketplace by making 100share round lots easier for small 
investors to buy furthermore the stamp of optimism they register 
is quite often reinforced with an accompanying increase in the 
dividend 
when such dividend increases are scarce as they are right now 
the bottomline impact is felt directly in calculations of 
investors total return capital appreciation plus current income 
at midyear the dividend yield on the 30 stocks that make up the 
dow jones industrial average stood at 374 percent compared with 
919 percent for a sampling of topgrade corporate bonds tracked by 
barrons magazine 
analysts say that wide competitive disparity helps put stock 
prices largely at the mercy of changes in interestrate 
expectations 
one note of consolation both stock splits and dividends right 
now show very little sign of the kind of speculative enthusiasm 
that is often cited as a warning of an impending top in stock 
prices 
so if you buy the optimistic view the current dearth of splits 
and dividend increases holds out hope that the best is yet to come 
for stocks 
end adv for monday july 9 
</TEXT>
